usa: President Warren G. Harding died of a heart attack at the Palace Hotel in San Francisco.<sup id="cite_ref-94" class="reference">[94]</sup>
Vice President Calvin Coolidge was sworn in as President, the day following the death of President Harding.<sup id="cite_ref-95" class="reference">[95]</sup>
Teapot Dome scandal: Secretary of the Interior Albert B. Fall resigned as a result of the scandal.[96]
The Equal Rights Amendment, written by women's suffragist leader Alice Paul, was first introduced in the Senate.[97]
